gujarati.context:
Sahu viitī rahyā vartāl, iyañ āvase lāḍīlō lāl;
Ēm vāṭ jūve sahu sāth, kahē jobane tedeja chhe nath.

Here is the translation:

He himself has taken care of his wife, he will get a red flag; 
Just look at him with companionship, says Joban that it was not so.

Here is the translation:

The day grants vision and becomes pleased; one's own slave is freed from sorrow;
Situated high on an eternal seat, I see my self, the same as a slave.

Here is the translation:

Happy life to those who are born, Shrawan Atithi on the eighth day; 
That is being celebrated by others, that job will be done when occupied.
